$ Python: <install-root>/Lib/site.py

`Lib/site.py` (located under the → development/languages/Python/installation/directory[Python root installation directory]) is a module that is automatically imported during → development/languages/Python initialization
(unless the → development/languages/Python/command-line/options[command line option] `-S` is specified).

This module appends *site-specific* paths of modules that are found under → development/languages/Python/installation/directory/Lib/site-packages[`Lib/site-packages`] to the module search path.

{ setquit()

  Among others, `site.py` has the function `setquit()` which defines the new(?) → development/languages/Python/built-in/functions[builtins](?) `quit` and `exit`.

}
